INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to prohibiting objects containing glass packaging or containers on or within 150 feet of a beach owned by the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting objects containing glass packaging or containers on or within 150 feet of a beach owned by the City of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring specific experience based qualifications for candidates nominated for appointment to serve on the Landmarks Preservation Commission.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring specific experience based qualifications for candidates nominated for appointment to serve on the Landmarks Preservation Commission.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution amending Resolution No. 538 (L.U. 197-A) adopted by the Council on September 27, 2006.
EventItemMatterName: Amending Resolution No. 538 (L.U. 197-A) adopted by the Council on September 27, 2006.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to reclassify Medgar Evers College as a four-year post-secondary institution for capital budget purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Reclassify Medgar Evers College as a four-year post-secondary institution for capital budget purposes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Congress to pass H.R. 2419, the Farm, Nutrition, and Bioenergy Act of 2007, which will increase the minimum food stamp grant, and the president to sign it into law.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass H.R. 2419, the Farm, Nutrition, and Bioenergy Act of 2007.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to adopt a Subway Riders Bill of Rights.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to adopt a Subway Riders Bill of Rights.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of City Planning to commence immediately a downzoning study of Carroll Gardens, Brooklyn and upon the Department of Buildings to implement the appropriate procedure so as to not issue permits that would allow any new construction or alteration to an existing building that would exceed a height limit of 50 feet until the Carroll Gardens neighborhood downzoning is complete.
EventItemMatterName: Commence immediately a downzoning study of Carroll Gardens, Brooklyn.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring the first week of October as “Arts Advocacy Week in Harlem.”
EventItemMatterName: Declaring the first week of October as “Arts Advocacy Week in Harlem.”

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring agency budgets and service statements to be published and filed electronically.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring agency budgets and service statements to be published and filed electronically.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to repaving streets.
EventItemMatterName: Repaving Streets

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York, the New York City Department of Transportation and the New York City Bureau of Traffic Enforcement to significantly increase fines and step up enforcement efforts for all traffic violations within the central business district of Manhattan in order to deter violators and help to effectively relieve traffic congestion and reduce air pollution.
EventItemMatterName: Significantly increase fines and step up enforcement efforts for all traffic violations within the central business district of Manhattan.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York, the New York City Department of Transportation and the New York City Planning Commission to increase the number of commercial loading zones within the central business district of Manhattan and to lawfully require off-street loading docks to be built when any new commercial buildings are constructed or substantially renovated within the central business district of Manhattan.
EventItemMatterName: Increase the number of commercial loading zones within the central business district of Manhattan.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey to impose two-way tolls for trucks on all crossings into and out of the City that are under its control for the purposes of removing the incentives for trucks to travel unnecessarily through the central business district of Manhattan to avoid the payment of tolls.
EventItemMatterName: Port Authority of New York and New Jersey to impose two-way tolls for trucks on all crossings into and out of the City that are under its control.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York and the New York City Department of Transportation to increase the number of metered parking spots within the non-residential areas of the central business district of Manhattan while also modestly increasing the rate of metered parking within the central business district of Manhattan.
EventItemMatterName: DOT to increase the number of metered parking spots within the non-residential areas of the central business district of Manhattan,

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to enact a one-third of one percent (.33%) payroll tax, to be imposed on businesses within the City of New York and within the surrounding counties of Nassau, Suffolk, Westchester and Rockland, and to create a regional authority to administer this revenue, which would be dedicated to improving and maintaining subways, commuter rails, highways, bridges and tunnels within the greater New York City region.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to enact a one-third of one percent (.33%) payroll tax, to be imposed on businesses within NYC and within the surrounding counties of Nassau, Suffolk, Westchester and Rockland.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to fully explore adopting legislation and/or regulatory measures to incentivize the immediate marketing and use of hydrogen fuel cell vehicles, to develop the re-fueling infrastructure to support these vehicles and to consider making the manufacture and importation of gasoline combustion vehicles unlawful by a date certain; and calling upon the city of New York to take steps to advance the use of hydrogen fuel cell technology and to find ways to  promote New York City as an economic center for hydrogen fuel cell technology.
EventItemMatterName: Explore adopting legislation and/or regulatory measures to incentivize the immediate marketing and use of hydrogen fuel cell vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York, the New York City Department of Transportation and the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to approve and institute a plan for the construction of a Trans-Narrows Tunnel between the boroughs of Brooklyn and Staten Island for the purposes of connecting the Staten Island railway to the New York City subway system.
EventItemMatterName: DOT and the MTA to approve and institute a plan for the construction of a Trans-Narrows Tunnel between the boroughs of Brooklyn and Staten Island.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York, the New York State Department of Transportation and the New York City Department of Transportation to approve and institute a plan for the construction of a Gowanus Expressway Tunnel to replace the elevated Gowanus Expressway.
EventItemMatterName: NYS DOT and the NYC DOT to approve and institute a plan for the construction of a Gowanus Expressway Tunnel.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York, the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey and the Federal government to approve and institute a plan for the construction of the Cross Harbor Freight Tunnel.
EventItemMatterName: Approve and institute a plan for the construction of the Cross Harbor Freight Tunnel.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York to relocate those City agencies that do not need to be in the central business district of Manhattan to outer borough neighborhoods that are near train lines with available capacity during rush hours.
EventItemMatterName: Relocate those City agencies that do not need to be in the central business district of Manhattan to outer borough neighborhoods.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York, the New York City Department of Transportation, and the New York City Taxi and Limousine Commission to significantly increase the number of taxi stands within the central business district of Manhattan and to equip such stands with all-weather furniture and shelter that would attract passengers to use such stands.
EventItemMatterName: DOT and TLC to significantly increase the number of taxi stands within the central business district of Manhattan.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to amend the Federal Runaway and Homeless Youth Act and implement regulations to increase the maximum eligible age for services to 24 years old from under 22 years old and to recognize the unique needs of LGBTQ runaway and homeless youth; and calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the State Runaway and Homeless Youth Act and implement regulations to increase the maximum eligible age for services to 24 years old from 21 years old, to recognize the unique needs of LGBTQ runaway and homeless youth, specifically by allowing, where appropriate, settings that are not gender segregated, to allow the maximum length of stay for youth in transitional independent living programs to be calculated independently of their 21st birthdays, to ease the 24-hour staffing requirement for residential programs, and to provide start-up grants for State certification applicants to use during the certification waiting period.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to amend the federal and State runaway and homeless youth acts.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel in diesel-powered generators used in the production of films, television programs and advertisements, and at street fairs in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel in diesel-powered generators used in the production of films, television programs and advertisements, and at street fairs in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing legal counsel for certain persons subject to eviction or foreclosure proceedings.
EventItemMatterName: Providing legal counsel for certain persons subject to eviction or foreclosure proceedings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring an annual report from the department of citywide administrative services detailing the status of unused city-owned real property.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring an annual report from the department of citywide administrative services detailing the status of unused city-owned real property.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to regulating construction operations occurring near landmarks.
EventItemMatterName: Regulating construction operations occurring near landmarks.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to the human rights law.
EventItemMatterName: Human Rights Law (protected class; affirmatively further fair housing)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting the Bloomberg Administration’s Lower Manhattan Security Initiative and its expansion of New York City surveillance cameras.
EventItemMatterName: Supporting the Bloomberg Administration’s Lower Manhattan Security Initiative and its expansion of New York City surveillance cameras.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to dismissing notices of violations issued to motor vehicles parked in front of illegal curb cuts.
EventItemMatterName: Dismissing notices of violations issued to motor vehicles parked in front of illegal curb cuts.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the registration of general contractors.
EventItemMatterName: Registration of general contractors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring certain buildings or structures to undergo a structural inspection.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring any building or structure that has been vacant for three years or longer to be inspected prior to the issuance of any permit to alter, repair, remove or enlarge that building or structure.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Governor of New York State and the New York State Legislature to adopt the recommendations of the Commission on the Future of Indigent Defense Services.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to adopt the recommendations of the Commission on the Future of Indigent Defense Services.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to permissible parking for certain purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Permissible parking for certain purposes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the New York city department of education to provide voter registration forms to all eighteen year old students.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the New York city department of education to provide voter registration forms to all eighteen year old students.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Senate to pass S. 3930, S. 3931, S. 3932 and S. 3933, which would protect the voting rights of the people of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Protect the voting rights of the people of New York. (S.3930, S.3931, S.3932 and S.3933)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the provision of services to people living with HIV and AIDS.
EventItemMatterName: Provision of services to people living with HIV and AIDS.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to enact A.2140/S.1312, an act to amend the education law in relation to allowing immunizing agents to be administered to adults by pharmacists.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the education law in relation to allowing immunizing agents to be administered to adults by pharmacists.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Legislature of the State of New York to amend New York State Public Officers Law to require that a person seeking municipal elective office in the City of New York be a resident of the political subdivision in which he/she is seeking election at least one year immediately preceding the election.
EventItemMatterName: Require that a person seeking municipal elective office in NYC be a resident of the political subdivision in which he/she is seeking election at least one year immediately preceding the election.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that the Department for the Aging fingerprint all employees at City senior centers for the purposes of conducting background investigations.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that the Department for the Aging fingerprint all employees at City senior centers for the purpose of conducting background investigations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Education (DOE) to institute a policy that would limit the aggregate amount of homework that is given to elementary and middle grade school children to approximately ten minutes per grade level on any given night, and would include a homework-free night to allow children to participate in other activities, exercise and spend quality time with their families.
EventItemMatterName: Dep't of Education to institute a policy that would limit the aggregate amount of homework that is given to elementary and middle grade school children to approximately ten minutes per grade level on any given night.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Legislature of the State of New York to amend the New York State Racing, Pari-Mutuel Wagering and Breeding Law to reduce State-imposed financial mandates on off-track betting corporations which have recently been absorbing a growing portion of the New York City Off-Track Betting Corporation’s revenues, driving the corporation into insolvency, and yielding no residual revenues for the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the New York State Racing, Pari-Mutuel Wagering and Breeding Law.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and adopt, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would authorize the city of New York to provide a personal income tax credit to residential homeowners who switch from oil to natural gas to heat their homes.
EventItemMatterName: Authorize NYC  to provide a personal income tax credit to residential homeowners who switch from oil to natural gas to heat their homes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the registration of vacant buildings and lots.
EventItemMatterName: Registration of vacant buildings and lots.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an annual survey of vacant and abandoned properties.
EventItemMatterName: An annual survey of vacant and abandoned properties.
